<div class="box">
<h2>How does this calculator work?</h2>
<p>
We assume you donate your income to the most effective health charities, as recommended by <a href="http://www.givingwhatwecan.org/">Giving What We Can</a>. </p>
<p>You can also find similar research from <a target="_blank" title="http://www.givewell.org/" href="http://www.givewell.org/">GiveWell</a>, which we recommend.</p>

<p>
A donation of £300 to the Stop TB Partnership is enough to prevent a death from tuberculosis. This is the figure we use to calculate how many lives you could save. It means that almost everyone living in a developed country has the power to save an incredible number of lives.
</p>

<p>
But there are health charities which are <a href="http://www.givingwhatwecan.org/resources/recommended-charities.php#SCI">even more cost effective</a>. Charities which prevent debilitating tropical diseases can buy someone 30 years of healthy life for only £60. They also significantly improve school attendance and earning power. Try playing around with Giving What We Can’s <a href="http://www.givingwhatwecan.org/resources/what-you-can-achieve.php">'what you can achieve'</a> calculator to see some more figures.
</p>

<p>
You might think it’s hard to donate so much of your income to charity, but you might not realise just how rich you are. Giving What We Can's <a href="http://www.givingwhatwecan.org/resources/how-rich-you-are.php">'how rich you are'</a> calculator can give you some concrete numbers.
</p>

</div>

